User shares content to recipient.id within
Partner App (using plugin recryption file strategy - post Sept. 2018 approach)

div.div: This approach eliminates the need to store a duplicate copy of the file containing 'Content' in advance. It uses a plug-in from Partner App that runs in the Stealthy App tray to do so.

The Partner App plug-in is served from the Partner App site and triggered by an argument along with a token from Stealthy Mobile (Stealthy Web in future too). Once loaded, the Partner App plug-in requires the user to sign in with Blockstack ID. That session data is stored in the Stealthy mobile App async storage so the user need not continue logging in.

The Partner App plug-in allows the Stealthy user (User.id) to choose on of their Partner App files and share it with a recipient (Recipient.id). If the Partner App has a public key look up system, it will decrypt the file and re-encrypt it with Recipient.id's public key, returning it to stealthy to either send as an attachment or store in User.id's gaia and send as a link.
More detail on this will follow in subsequent diagrams.

div.style: display: inline-block; font-size: 12px; font-family: Helvetica; color: rgb(0, 0, 0); line-height: 1.2; vertical-align: top; width: 218px; white-space: normal; word-wrap: normal;

div.div: The main benefit of this approach is that now Partner App files can be shared at any time through stealthy with any Blockstack user, without having to go back to Partner App to explicitly share and save again.
